{"id": "duc04-testb-14:6#20", "contents": "The situation in Kosovo remains dire, with Yugoslav forces reportedly increasing their attacks on ethnic Albanians despite a U.N. resolution demanding a cease-fire. U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan reported apparent violations of the resolution and decried the \"appalling atrocities in Kosovo.\" The U.N. chief also noted that rebel forces of the Kosovo Liberation Army were responsible for human rights violations, a charge the KLA quickly denied. As tensions escalate, Yugoslavia's prime minister warned that the country was \"faced with the imminent danger of war\" and called on parliament to conclude that Yugoslavia must defend itself if attacked."}
